def has_two_cube_sums(n):
    cubes = [i**3 for i in range(1, round(n**(1/3)) + 1)]
    cube_sums = [(i, j) for i in range(len(cubes)) for j in range(i, len(cubes)) if cubes[i] + cubes[j] <= n]
    valid_sums = [(cubes[i], cubes[j]) for i, j in cube_sums if cubes[i] + cubes[j] == n]
    valid_sums = [tuple(sorted(pair)) for pair in valid_sums]
    unique_sums = list(set(valid_sums))
    return len(unique_sums) > 1
